---
description: Error handling standards
globs: ["src/**/*.{ts,tsx}"]
alwaysApply: false
---
- Never swallow errors; propagate with `throw` or a `Result<T, E>` pattern.
- HTTP handlers translate errors to **RFC 9457 Problem Details** JSON.
- Use exponential back-off retry for transient I/O failures (e.g. `async-retry`).
